Ha! Turns out that lot of the links are carbon copies from someone else's game strategy submission so they're going to try to legitimately classify as an AI but with just a tiny coding change to make the game from the Battle Snake game that said submission was based heavily on. Everyone was probably a bit shocked when someone that was on full paid had already beaten Battle Snake.

After that, the next person using the Pokkwan strategy released somewhere else could also bring some fun provided the Pokkwan commands weren't easier to use than the Battle Snake commands.

At the time of this rationale, I had already posted a Snake guide using an AI tool I had.  I also took the opportunity to take some motivation from the disappointed look on people's faces as they continued to lose to a human bot (even though you could beat it fairly easily) by posting examples of the latest game they had played. Then, someone made the comment "How do you get died all the time?".

It got people to carefully read each step on the elephant picture which included "Typical easy run into wall" which made for a decent laugh.

I added to that by posting a screen shot of actual Amazon comments that were left by people who had finally grokked what was going on and were well along with understanding how to control the AI. **END LAST RATIONALE**
